Program: Discovery
Title: World Ocean's day
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwwt
Last Broadcast Date: 09 June 1997
A report on the sea to mark World Ocean's day. The programme looks at how the colour of the sea is dictated by plankton and how bacteria plays a part in the tropical oceans where nutrients are scarce, often they can absorb nitrogen and make their own food.